cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about a family of multitask variational methods for semi-supervised sequence labeling, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a generative model and a discriminative labeler, which are common techniques in machine learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the use of latent variables and hierarchical structures in the models may indicate relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of word embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
